{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"<time>","mdn_url":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/HTML/Element/time","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"resumo","title":"Resumo","isH3":false,"content":"<p>O elemento HTML <em>time</em>&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: inherit;\">(</span><code style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit;\">&lt;time&gt;</code><span style=\"line-height: inherit;\">) representa o tempo tanto no formato de 24 horas ou como uma data precisa no calendário Gregoriano (com informações&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: inherit;\">opcionais&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: inherit;\">de tempo e fuso horário)</span></p>\n\n<p>Este elemento é destinado a apresentar datas e horas no dispositivo em um formato legível<span style=\"line-height: inherit;\">. Isto pode ser útil aos agentes do usuário em oferecer qualquer programação de eventos ao calendário do utilizador.</span></p>\n\n<div class=\"note notecard\" id=\"sect1\"><strong>Notas de uso:</strong> Este elemento não é adequado por exemplo, quando uma data específica não pode ser calculada, e nem deveria ser utilizado em datas anteriores ao calendário Gregoriano (devido as complicações com os cálculos dessas datas).</div>\n\n<div class=\"note notecard\" id=\"sect2\"><strong>Nota de estatus:</strong>&nbsp;Este elemento foi concebido e está em discussão desde 2011 (<a class=\"external\" href=\"http://blog.whatwg.org/weekly-time-data\" rel=\" noopener\">http://blog.whatwg.org/weekly-time-data</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">)</span></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"contexto_de_uso","title":"Contexto de uso","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Content_categories\" title=\"HTML/Content categories\">Categorias de conteúdo</a></td>\n   <td><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Content_categories#flow_content\" title=\"HTML/Content categories#Flow content\">flow content</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Content_categories#phrasing_content\" title=\"HTML/Content categories#Phrasing content\">phrasing content</a></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td>Permitted content</td>\n   <td><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Content_categories#phrasing_content\" title=\"HTML/Content categories#Phrasing content\">Phrasing content</a>, but no descendant <code>time</code> elements.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td>Tag omission</td>\n   <td>None, both the start tag and the end tag are mandatory.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td>Permitted parent elements</td>\n   <td>Any element that accepts phrasing content.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td>Normative document</td>\n   <td><a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/multipage/text-level-semantics.html#the-time-element\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener\">HTML5, section 4.6.10</a></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"atributos","title":"Atributos","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Como todo&nbsp;outro&nbsp;elemento&nbsp;HTML, este elemento suporta os <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes\">atributos globais</a>.</p>\n\n<dl>\n <dt id=\"datetime\"><a id=\"attr-datetime\" href=\"#attr-datetime\"><b><code>datetime</code></b></a></dt>\n <dd>Esse atributo indica a hora e a data do elemento e deve ser uma data válida com uma string de tempo opcional. Se o valor não puder ser analisado como uma data com uma string de tempo opcional, o elemento não possui um timestamp associado.</dd>\n <dt id=\"pubdate\"><a id=\"attr-pubdate\" href=\"#attr-pubdate\"><b><code>pubdate</code></b></a></dt>\n <dd>(This feature is still being discussed by the WHATWG and the W3C HTML5 Working Group.) This Boolean attribute specifies that the date and time given by the element is the publication date of a document. The document it applies to is either the nearest ancestor article element or the document as a whole (if there is no ancestor <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/article\" title=\"HTML/Element/Article\">article</a> element). If true, the <code>time</code> element must have a corresponding date. Additionally, each <code>time</code> element indicating a publication date must be the only <code>time</code> element that does so for that document.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"dom_interface","title":"DOM interface","isH3":false,"content":"<p>This element implements the <code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTimeElement\" title=\"DOM/HTMLTimeElement\">HTMLTimeElement</a></code> interface.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"exemplos","title":"Exemplos","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"simple_example","title":"Simple example","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>The concert starts at <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>time</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>20:00<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>time</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>.<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Above HTML will output:</p>\n\n<p>The concert starts at 20:00.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"pubdate_example","title":"<code>pubdate</code> example","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>article</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>This article was created on <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>time</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">pubdate</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>2011-01-28<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>time</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>.<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>article</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Above HTML will output:</p>\n\n<p>This article was created on 2011-01-28.</p>","titleAsText":"pubdate example"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"datetime_example","title":"<code>datetime</code> example","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>The concert took place on <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>time</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">datetime</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>2001-05-15 19:00<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>May 15<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>time</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>.<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Above HTML will output:</p>\n\n<p>The concert took place on May 15.</p>","titleAsText":"datetime example"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"compatibilidade","title":"Compatibilidade","isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect3\"><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/mdn/browser-compat-data\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Estamos convertendo nossos dados de compatibilidade para o formato JSON</a></strong>.\n            Esta tabela de compatibilidade ainda usa o formato antigo,\n            pois ainda não convertemos os dados que ela contém.\n            <strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Structures/Compatibility_tables\" class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\">Descubra como você pode ajudar! (en-US)</a></strong></div>\n\n<div class=\"htab\" id=\"sect4\">\n    <a id=\"AutoCompatibilityTable\" name=\"AutoCompatibilityTable\"></a>\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"selected\"><a href=\"#compat-desktop\">Desktop</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"#compat-mobile\">Dispositivo móvel</a></li>\n    </ul>\n</div><p></p>\n\n<div id=\"compat-desktop\">\n<table class=\"compat-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th>Feature</th>\n   <th>Chrome</th>\n   <th>Firefox (Gecko)</th>\n   <th>Internet Explorer</th>\n   <th>Opera</th>\n   <th>Safari</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td>Basic support</td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span style=\"color:#f00;\">Não suportado</span> <a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=629801\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;629801</a></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td>11.50</td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"compat-mobile\">\n<table class=\"compat-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th>Feature</th>\n   <th>Android</th>\n   <th>Firefox Mobile (Gecko)</th>\n   <th>IE Mobile</th>\n   <th>Opera Mobile</th>\n   <th>Safari Mobile</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td>Basic support</td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span style=\"color:#f00;\">Não suportado</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Veja também","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/#the-time-element\" rel=\" noopener\">The <code>time</code> element</a> (HTML5 specification)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Resumo","id":"resumo"},{"text":"Contexto de uso","id":"contexto_de_uso"},{"text":"Atributos","id":"atributos"},{"text":"DOM interface","id":"dom_interface"},{"text":"Exemplos","id":"exemplos"},{"text":"Compatibilidade","id":"compatibilidade"},{"text":"Veja também","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"O elemento HTML time (<time>) representa o tempo tanto no formato de 24 horas ou como uma data precisa no calendário Gregoriano (com informações opcionais de tempo e fuso horário)","popularity":0.0003,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"<time>","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch"},{"title":"<time>: The (Date) Time element","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"time","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"<time>","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"<time>","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"<time>","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"<time>","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"<time>","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"<time>","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"pt-br/web/html/element/time","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/pt-br/web/html/element/time/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/pt-BR/docs/Web","title":"Tecnologia Web para desenvolvedores"},{"uri":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/HTML","title":"HTML: Linguagem de Marcação de Hipertexto"},{"uri":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/HTML/Element","title":"Elementos HTML"},{"uri":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/HTML/Element/time","title":"<time>"}],"pageTitle":"<time> - HTML: Linguagem de Marcação de Hipertexto | MDN","noIndexing":false}}